Okay.  The player S scenario.   I am going to ASSUME you are TRYING to refer to player 'S' as a generic player. However, I will point out that while it starts that way, it does move from sounding like a general player 's' scenario to a specific individual who has done you wrong.   I will go with the generic player 's' since I am sure you wish to stop exploitingin all forms, and not just becaue of one person.  If it is the latter, that is just vindictive nonsense.  So lets go with generic player 's'<br>
