This is someone who either has the time, the ambition, the drive, the insanity, or the lack of a life, to be the best he can be in the world of Erollisi Marr.  Maybe you left out something, but nothing in this description indicates an exploiter.   Just because someone has taken to learn how the game works,  know what to kill and when, and knows where and how to get stuff... this makes them a skilled player, not an exploiter. (Relax, there is more to this, remember I am trying to tie it together as I go...)<br>
<br>
Personally I know a TON of mechanics and things as to how the game works, and use them to the best of my advantage. I often solo (not sharing exp) and know exactly where to go to get good items easy and fast.  Does this make me an exploiter?  I hardly think so.<br>
<br>
<br>
So this alone, is not a good assertation for leading to an exploiter.   The comment about you can assume he is wililng to exploit, is a bad one, a misleading one,  there is nothing in the profile to lead to that assumption fairly.<br>
