- this guys is literally 20 levels ahead of the CLOSEST players who is actually a freind of his. <br>
- He is TOTALLY beyond the pale of the other players.<br>
But he IS able to get the goodies that people want. <br>
- The other players cannot get the stuff on their own.<br>
   ** Is this jsut a statement of fact? or are you implying it is because of player S they cannot do it?<br>
<br>
- So he introduces one of the oldest scams know to man. Political Patronage. He has to be a great guy cause he gave me all this kool stuff!<br>
     ** I must differ with you on this.  To succeed in EQ you cannot solo your whole existance.  Even in the beginning, you need a group around you.  A guild.  There are many ways to do this,  one of which is winning the hearts of the people.  It is completely acceptable, and not a scam in anyway to provide favors in exchange for companionship/loyalty.<br>
<br>
- Because people are apparently sheep, they dont ask very many questions about how that happens.<br>
     ** Why would they? He is higher level than they are, they have no idea what is involved.  There is no reason they would be considered sheep.  If they cant get it, and someone is willing to give it to them, why should they question the hows and whys?  Just curious.  I as a high level often handed off items to my guildmates, or to newbies, because I could.  Not one of them was obtained through sinister methods, or with ulterior motives.  I think this is more of a person view/grudge than a sensible explanation.<br>
<br>
- BUT more importantly, this player, NO LONGER NEEDS TO EXPLOIT. He doesnt have to. <br>
   ** You still have not said where he was exploiting?  Again, knowing how the game works, knowing what to fight and when, and getting the good stuff does not in anyway equate to exploiting.  EVEN him knowing the exploits, does not in any way equate to him using them.  You have not stated where he was exploiting.<br>
- Since mostly no one saw him doing it(hes a necro you recall)<br>
    ** Again, how does him being a necro apply?  If noone saw him doign it, then noone saw him doing it. His class has no bearing on the matter and only suggests some bigotry towards necros. (Not saying you are, saying it suggests).<br>
- If he is accused, he can demand proof(by his standards) <br>
    ** And rightfully so.<br>
- There are kill logs and some ARE examined, and some questions ARE asked, but that information doesnt filter down to the players. <br>
    ** Kill logs will not reveal exploitation in and of themselves as they just show mobs killed they are not that detailed really.  Also, there is no obligation by the GMs and or guides to relay any info to the players.  In fact, in most cases that just makes it worse.<br>
<br>
- Only those 'outside' know. But since no GM ever caught him red-handed he is teflon. <br>
     ** Rightfully so,  GM's are not gods, they are not as all powerful as people think.  If they cannot prove he did it,  then they have no place pinning him for doing it. This is common sense.<br>
<br>
- Of course his closest freind are NOT anywhere near as carefull as this guy, and they DO get caught, repeatedly.<br>
  **  If they truly do get caught repeatedly,  the GMs have in the past been very good about dictating proper repricussions (sp?). <br>
<br>
- It kind of stains the image so he broaden his patronage.<br>
  ** Not sure about this,  not real sure what you mean to be sayig here.<br>
<br>
- In the end he has his own little sycophants, who all owe him their position, and they will defend him until death. Even tho they know the score. There is NOTHING they wont do, for this guy. Loyalty in action.<br>
   **  This is not the fault of player S.  This is teh fault of the people who are giving a nobody their undeniable loyalty.  However,  if these people are all of like mind.  Meaning they all want everything they can, and be all they can be, then of course they will follow without question someone who can take them there.  That is normal leadership/followship dynamics.<br>
<br>
<br>
 - Worse, they are the most arrogant dicks in the game. They dont mind showing their power to ANYONE who is foolish enough to cross them.<br>
    ** Personal opinion here COMPLETELY.  I know MANY MANY uber people and guilds, and while some are indeed very arrogant,  the guild is not arrogant because of a couple of players.  Again, my opinion vs yours.  Showing their power to any foolish enough to cross them?   I am goign to stay away from this one for now.<br>
<br>
-- Except for that one obnoxious guy over in the corner that keeps pointing out some unpleasant facts. Keeps asking about certain events that we dont want to talk about.<br>
     ** What facts are we talking about?  That he knows the game?  That he knows what to kill and when to kill it and what to get and where?  That he has devoted followers who will do what he wants because he can take them where they want to go?  Well, uhm.. . I would be pissed too.  If this person kept on me and my guild because we knew our @#%$ and what not,  Sure I would be pissed as well.<br>
<br>
You then say he created a power block by exploiting.  That would not be there if he hadn't exploited.  Again, I must point out that you did NOT poitn out any situation in which he exploited.  It is also unfair to assume that he is not skilled, and could very well be in power positions purly on his skill.  You are insinuating here that anyone UBER in a controlling position is exploiting.  That is not fair.<br>
<br>
----------- Now as I said,  there was more in relation to other stuff so here is where that comes in. .  To those reading this post thinking,  GOD this is to F'n long. . I did warn you up top,  and it is longer, so have some more tea and biscuts, but  I did try to protect you from this if you didnt care =)<br>
-------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
So,  to sum up the first scenario you put up,  there was nothing in there to suggest exploitative behavior accept your saying you can assume he is willing to exploit.  HOWEVER...<br>
<br>
Later you say to Carthos that your awareness of this person comes from an event in Unrest on day 26 of the server.  What was this event?   It apparently killed TONS of people, but what was this event that leveled him SO quickly?  Not saying it didnt happen,  just wondering what it was?  Again however I must ask clearly. . . . are we talking exploitatin in GENERAL?   Or are we talking about a specific person?   <br>
<br>
I am sure you can see there may be some confusion.  IF you say this is caused by, because of, all due to,  centered on, related to and with   a specific person ,  I am ending the conversation with your response and paying you no heed in the future.   Vindictiveness and Revenge are not appealing traits and that is what it would be.   <br>
<br>
IF you are going to continue with exploitation in GENERAL whcih is what your crusade implicates,  I will continue to talk as much as you would like.  I hope that was clear.<br>
<br>
So, this little tidbit does add some,  you see a person engage in exploitative behavior.  What did you do?  Did you bring it to the attention of the GMs?   Did they ignore you .. if they did they were in the wrong.  Did they come and talk, and TRY to come to a conclusion but there was not enough to go on?  If they did they tried, but you really cannot fault them for not making a decsion based on events they cannot verify. <br>
<br>
-----------------------<br>
Still later<br>
-----------------------<br>
<br>
You then make a comment that killing a soul devourer who is stuck in a door and cannot fight back is exploitative.<br>
<br>
BINGO!  You have NOW stated a bonafied, verifiable, exploit.  THIS is indeed an exploit.  How this killed 64 people I will never understand, but this is indeed an exploit.  <br>
<br>
However, a soul devourer in unrest is hardly going to take you to 50th level and earn you the admiration of the server.  So what else is missing here?<br>
<br>
--------------------------------<br>
<br>
So, that was in response to your posting so far.  I really am trying to fit into your mindset butyou really are giving nothign to work on.<br>
<br>
I do want to reiterate, because this is very important.<br>
<br>
IF this whole conversation is going to be about the incidents and actions of A SPECIFIC person, then your crusade is not against abusive players, but is against AN abusive player.  It then is not a crusade, but a one man lynch mob and I cannot be part of that.  That is silly.<br>
<br>
However,  if your crusade IS truly against exploiters in general,  abusive behavioral patterns and the like,  I will continue to talk with ya.<br>
-----------------------------------------------<br>
Exploiting,  is using a flaw in the games mechanics to ones advantage where there is little to no chance of death or harm and above average chance of gains outside normal actions.<br>
<br>
Learning how the game works, and using that information is not exploiting.  You know how to play the game which should be the goal of everyone.<br>
<br>
Learning what and where to fight is not exploiting, it is making good use of your time and your skills.<br>
<br>
Learning where to get the cool stuff, is not exploiting, it is also making good use of your time and skills.<br>
<br>
All of the above by the way make you an outstanding player, a useful player, and a sought after player.  Noone should be condemned for that.<br>
<br>
I also have not met anyone who has made their entire level career based on exploits.  Some skill has to be involved, it is impossible otherwise really.<br>
<br>
Now,  it is late. . I am beat. . . spent the day at a county fair (want to see a very diverse cross section of very scary people. . hit a conty fair)<br>
<br>
Till later,  enjoy.<br>
